history.content: 162+184+188 in summer is an extremely high workload. If you can do well, then I guess you can handle 189+170+127. 189, 170, 127 are theory heavy. I cannot guarantee you can handle these three courses if your coding is much better than theory. Now that you have taken 162, I think 161 is more useful.

children.subject: 127 is better. Professor Sahai's 189 is difficult. Taking 127 concurrently helps.
OK. But should I take cs 161 or ee 127?

history.content: I don't plan to career in security. Which of cs161 and 169a should I take if I can only take one?
history.subject: Choosing Between CS161 and CS169A

history.content:
Hi. I am an in-coming junior who has finished the EECS lower-div's and CS 162, 184, and 188. In this up coming fall, I want to take CS 189, 170, and EE 127, but I am currently enrolled in CS 189, 170, 161, 169A.

I am #40 in the waitlist for EE 127, so just in case I don't make it, I need to decide between CS 161 and 169A. I don't think I want to career in security but rather machine learning or AI. Is 169A preferred to 161?

Also I am not quite sure if EE 127, CS 170, and CS 189 is a viable workload. I took my three upper-divs in this summer session if that tells anything.

Also I don't mind if you ask about my performance in any courses.
history.subject: Choosing Between CS161 and CS169A
